{
  "answer": "**Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 41** addresses defiling acts (*malāvaha*), specifically listing the killing of birds, aquatic animals, those born in water, worms, and insects, as well as eating food associated with liquor.[^1][^2]\n\nThese acts are proscribed as defiling.[^3] The central prescriptive rule is that purification (*prāyaścitta*) for such acts requires undergoing either the *taptakṛcchra* penance or the more severe *kṛcchrātikṛcchra*.[^4]\n\n[^1]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 41, [paragraph](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/41/translation/#p-17a394).\n[^2]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 41, [passage](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/41/translation/#p-ef13c5-p-bbb63f).\n[^3]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 41, [paragraph](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/41/translation/#p-572d18).\n[^4]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 41, [paragraph](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/41/translation/#p-8818cd).",
